Was real surprised with this one as I have not been a fan of any of this brewery's beers. But this one nailed it. Subtle English esters and the perfect bitterness and late hops. Great British style pale.

Just a middle of the road beer. Had enough cherry to it to call it a cherry beer. But almost no additions to taste from the wheat

Light roasty, slight hop bitterness. Thin but not too thin. Once it warms a bit chocolate comes thru.

Wow what an aroma. Thinner for a stout but a stout non the less. Great beer.

Oh I like this. Coffee and chocolate notes. Got a fuggles like aura about it. And a bitterness that's perfect. Easily my favorite beer on the menu.

I think this is the best version of this beer yet. Clove and slight banana. The wheat really comes thru.

This beer has so many tastes coming at you. Some of them dont seem to mix with each other. But pretty good on a hot day like today.
Dont like this beer at all. Not too many beers I can say that too. Tried both cold and warm. Something in the taste. cardboady maybe.
I like this beer, but it tastes exactly like the IPA with out all the hops. same feel same color.
Not really an IPA guy but I really like this. Almost like a hidden chocolate tone to it. Maybe some prunes or something in the back ground. Not Bitter, but hop flavor all over.

Good little beer. Nothing over the top just solid all around. Bit hazy, but does not detract much from this great tasting beer. Getting another one.

Smokey aroma.  Taste is all over the place. Nutty, caramel, coffee. Maybe even chewing tobacco.  Sharp dryness. Just a great beer.

Wow. Coriander comes thru the dryness. Dry feel but still sweet. Citrusy. Right at the last second you get a saltiness. Like this beer.

It ok. Nothing special sticks out about it. Almost seems like a watered down version of Kingfisher beer. A bit lighter though so could drink a few of these
Goes mighty fine with curry. Sort of thicker mouth feels a bit out of place. If I could find it at beer store i would buy it.

Yea its a pilsner. Tastes like a beer. Nothing great nothing bad just a decent beer

Lemony and a bit of hop bite. Lemony aromas would be good, but closely mimics lemon dish soap. But I do like this beer.

Excellent beer. Balanced out just about right. For my tastes it could be a smidge sweeter or maybe more A touch more Munich, But great just the way it is. One of the best on the menu right now

Wow. I thought I might have had a bad bottle, but they all taste like bloody tinfoil or something. Tried from bottle, pint glass, plastic cup. Nope bloody tinfoil. Even the smell is metallic. forced 3 down. no more

Far better on tap than bottle from the bottle. Don't know why, just is. Nothing stands out with this beer, just a solid great tasting beer. Proves that you don't need a niche over the top angle to beer a great beer.
